The Truth About вҖңReal DataвҖқ in Your Setup

You do not need a real robot.
Everything is simulated inside Python using your SO101Env environment.

You do not need to open MuJoCo GUI.
MuJoCo runs in the background to simulate physics. You call it through your environment with env.reset() and env.step(action).

You do not manually record data.
Your replay buffer is filled automatically when you run your collect_trajectories or collect_sequence functions. These generate вҖңreal simulated trajectoriesвҖқ from MuJoCo.

The .xml file is still needed, but only for the simulation definition.

It tells MuJoCo what the robot looks like and how it behaves.

You donвҖҷt open it yourself; the environment reads it when SO101Env initializes:

self.model = mujoco.MjModel.from_xml_path(model_path)
self.data = mujoco.MjData(self.model)

If the file isnвҖҷt there, you get the ParseXML: Error opening file 'so101.xml' error вҖ” you just need the file in the right path.

Actions can start random.
At first, your replay buffer will store sequences generated by random actions. Later, your actor network will generate smarter actions.



